	h2 A walk in the woods
	.story After breakfast, we gathered at the front of the hall for gentle snowshoeing. A snowshoe is small floatation device that you attach to your shoes creating a large surface area and assisting you in walking over snow. It is especially useful when walking in deep snow as your legs do not sink in as much. We hiked through the forest beside the hotel. 
	.story It was hauntingly silent. The air was still and there were no signs of life. No chirping of birds or rustling of leaves. Whatever sound that is left, the snow absorbed it all. All you could hear was the ringing white noise and the sound of your breath. Looking around, things and landscape were either white or black. Such was the bleak yet indescribable beauty of the winter.
