	h2 Paatsjoki River
	.story Tonight's activity was aurora hunting with two local guides. We got onto a van as snow started falling. Soon we were speeding down the dark road towards the border that Finland shared with Russia. We stopped next to the border checkpoint and the guide shared the history between the two countries. Next stop, we headed to the iconic bridge across the Paatsjoki river.  Alas, the weather was not cooperative, there was no aurora. Making best of the situation, we took photos of the river. The Paatsjoki river flows out of Lake Inari into Russia is not frozen in the cold winter.
