	h2 Aurora Borealis 
	.story My half-opened sleepy eyes caught a glimpse of green light through a small crack in the snow-covered glass ceiling. Could it be an aurora? I stumbled towards the edge of the window and peeped through the crack. I immediately woke Ellis up. It was 5.30 am and a flurry of activity in the glass igloo. We dressed into out wooly bear suits, gathered the cameras and dashed out.
	.story You can read about it, watched them a hundred times on YouTube and the aurora still takes your breath away the first time you see. It dances. Oh how the light dances. Each ebb and flow were gracefully executed across the sky. The stars now became a beautiful backdrop. The colors of the aurora were like florescent paints swirling through the cosmic medium. Staring awestruck at the sky, the aurora was perceptibly larger and closer. All these lasted only for twenty minutes before the heavy clouds rolled in.
